sec.p:
This sensing paradigm has several inherent advantages:
It does not require line-of-sight or visual tracking, making it robust to occlusion or poor lighting conditions;
The system can operate with minimal electronics since the mechanical motion directly influences the RF response;
No complex data processing is required, as the relevant information is embedded in the transmission coefficients of the link (i.e., the parameter S21 of the scattering matrix of the link).
